  "text": "Increased susceptibility of Dacron to colonization in vitro was usually caused by its greater porosity than that of PTFP. Smoothing the Dacron surface with gelatin makes it less susceptible to infections in a mouse model [CITATION_1] . For polyester implants, we did not observe the influence of the treatment with gelatin or gelatin and silver ions on the number of implant associated bacteria (1 vs 2, and 1 vs 7, Fig. 1B) .",
